!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

authentic /ɔːˈθɛntɪk/

1. ADJ An authentic person, object, or emotion is genuine. 真实的 

例： ...authentic Italian food. …正宗的意大利食品。 

例： She has authentic charm whereas most people simply have nice manners. 她有真正的魅力，而大多数人只是有礼貌而已。 

2. authenticity N-UNCOUNT 真实性 

例： There are factors, however, that have cast doubt on the statue's authenticity. 然而，有些因素已经让人们对这座雕像的真实性产生了怀疑。 

3. ADJ If you describe something as authentic , you mean that it is such a good imitation that it is almost the same as or as good as the original. 逼真的 [表赞许] 

例： ...patterns for making authentic frontier-style clothing. …制作地道的边疆风格服装的图样。 

4. ADJ An authentic piece of information or account of something is reliable and accurate. 可靠的 

例： I had obtained the authentic details about the birth of the organization. 我已经弄到了有关该组织成立的可靠的详细资料。

</div>

